831Local<Data> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
832#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
833 using A = internal::Address;
834 using I = internal::Internals;
835 A obj = internal::ValueHelper::ValueAsAddress(this);
836 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
837 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
838 int instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
839 if (I::CanHaveInternalField(instance_type)) {
840 int offset = I::kJSAPIObjectWithEmbedderSlotsHeaderSize +
841 (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
842 A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(obj, offset);
843#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
844 // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
845 // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
846 value = I::DecompressTaggedField(obj, static_cast<uint32_t>(value));
847#endif
848
849 auto isolate = reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(
850 internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(obj));
851 return Local<Data>::New(isolate, value);
852 }
853#endif
854 return SlowGetInternalField(index);
855}
856
857void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(v8::Isolate* isolate,
858 int index) {
859#if !defined(V8_ENABLE_CHECKS)
860 using A = internal::Address;
861 using I = internal::Internals;
862 A obj = internal::ValueHelper::ValueAsAddress(this);
863 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
864 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
865 auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
866 if (V8_LIKELY(I::CanHaveInternalField(instance_type))) {
867 int offset = I::kJSAPIObjectWithEmbedderSlotsHeaderSize +
868 (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index) +
869 I::kEmbedderDataSlotExternalPointerOffset;
870 A value =
871 I::ReadExternalPointerField<internal::kEmbedderDataSlotPayloadTag>(
872 isolate, obj, offset);
873 return reinterpret_cast<void*>(value);
874 }
875#endif
876 return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(isolate, index);
877}
878
879void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
880#if !defined(V8_ENABLE_CHECKS)
881 using A = internal::Address;
882 using I = internal::Internals;
883 A obj = internal::ValueHelper::ValueAsAddress(this);
884 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
885 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
886 auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
887 if (V8_LIKELY(I::CanHaveInternalField(instance_type))) {
888 int offset = I::kJSAPIObjectWithEmbedderSlotsHeaderSize +
889 (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index) +
890 I::kEmbedderDataSlotExternalPointerOffset;
891 Isolate* isolate = I::GetIsolateForSandbox(obj);
892 A value =
893 I::ReadExternalPointerField<internal::kEmbedderDataSlotPayloadTag>(
894 isolate, obj, offset);
895 return reinterpret_cast<void*>(value);
896 }
897#endif
898 return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
899}

901// static
902template <CppHeapPointerTag tag, typename T>
903T* Object::Unwrap(v8::Isolate* isolate, const v8::Local<v8::Object>& wrapper) {
904 auto obj = internal::ValueHelper::ValueAsAddress(*wrapper);
905#if !defined(V8_ENABLE_CHECKS)
906 return internal::ReadCppHeapPointerField<tag, T>(
907 isolate, obj, internal::Internals::kJSObjectHeaderSize);
908#else // defined(V8_ENABLE_CHECKS)
909 return reinterpret_cast<T*>(Unwrap(isolate, obj, tag));
910#endif // defined(V8_ENABLE_CHECKS)
911}
912
913// static
914template <CppHeapPointerTag tag, typename T>
915T* Object::Unwrap(v8::Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<Object>& wrapper) {
916 auto obj =
917 internal::ValueHelper::ValueAsAddress(wrapper.template value<Object>());
918#if !defined(V8_ENABLE_CHECKS)
919 return internal::ReadCppHeapPointerField<tag, T>(
920 isolate, obj, internal::Internals::kJSObjectHeaderSize);
921#else // defined(V8_ENABLE_CHECKS)
922
923 return reinterpret_cast<T*>(Unwrap(isolate, obj, tag));
924#endif // defined(V8_ENABLE_CHECKS)
925}
